  "text": "Patients with cancer-induced weight loss show reduced protein synthesis in skeletal muscle [CITATION_1] and increased protein degradation, with the latter resulting from an increased expression of the ubiquitin-proteasome proteolytic pathway, the major determinant of protein degradation. In agreement with this, skeletal muscle from cachectic cancer patients shows increased expression of mRNA for ubiquitin [CITATION_2] and the proteasome subunits [CITATION_3] with proteasome-mediated proteolytic activity increasing in parallel with ubiquitin expression [CITATION_4] . As in cancer cachexia, there was a marked increase in chymot-",
